Help [=[

matrix.copy(m [, x])
--------------------

Returns a copy of `m` and optionally sets its content to `x`, a number.
`matrix.copy` is semantically equivalent to

        function matrix.copy (m, x)
          local c = matrix.new(matrix.shape(m, 1, true)) -- frame
          return set(c, x or m)
        end

__See also__: `matrix.set`
]=]
